---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us - useUtils" 
  description="Discover the mission behind useUtils. We build beautiful, local-first tools for developers that respect privacy."
  keywords="about useutils, developer tools privacy, secure developer utilities"
>
  <Header />

  <!-- Main Body Content -->
  <main class="flex-grow w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pt-2 pb-6 border-b border-border-hairline/60">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 font-sans">
        About us
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
        The story and mission behind useUtils: building tools developers actually trust.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          The Mission
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          Software engineers paste sensitive payloads, API tokens, database schemas, and configs into random online tools every single day. Most web utilities transmit this data to remote servers, tracking logs and capturing keys. We built <strong class="text-zinc-200">useUtils</strong> to prove that developer tools, playground runtimes, configs, and labs can be robust, visually stunning, and completely local-first.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          Privacy First, by Architecture
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          We enforce privacy through our application topology. Every utility, interactive WASM compiler, and visual code scaffold executes entirely inside your browser sandbox. WebRTC-based sharing coordinates direct point-to-point data streams without staging file metadata on any server.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          Five Hub Workspaces
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          To build an indispensable workspace, we support five high-value spaces: <strong class="text-zinc-200">Developer Tools</strong> (100+ micro-utilities), <strong class="text-zinc-200">Playground</strong> (WASM compilers & runtimes), <strong class="text-zinc-200">Cheatsheets</strong> (high-density references), <strong class="text-zinc-200">Labs</strong> (WebRTC experiments), and <strong class="text-zinc-200">Configs</strong> (interactive boilerplate builder).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          Raycast Design System
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          We draw inspiration from modern developer desk applications like Raycast to ensure useUtils feels premium: dark velvety charcoal layouts (`#151515`), thin zinc borders, monospaced tokens, emerald highlights, and custom keyboard hotkeys to navigate the spaces cleanly.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
